{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/exports"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variants","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RunningInEditor"],"title":"Articles and Tutorials","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This document deals with exporting properties, for information about exposing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions to the Godot world, see the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","isActive":true},{"text":" document.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Introduction-to-Exports","text":"Introduction to Exports","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The simplest way of exporting a variable is to annotate it with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Export","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"attribute, like this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftGodot","","@Godot","public class ExportExample: Node3D","{","    @Export","    var number = 5","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In that example the value 5 will be saved, and after building the current"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"project it will be visible in the property editor."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One of the fundamental benefits of exporting member variables is to have them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"visible and editable in the editor. This way, artists and game designers can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modify values that later influence how the program runs. For this, a special export syntax is provided."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Exporting can only be applied to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"},{"text":"-compatible types.  The Godot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"core-structures and classes, as well as objects that subclass "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Export"},{"type":"text","text":" macro only works in your class definition, and will not work"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on Swift class extensions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Basic Usage","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Basic-Usage"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Exporting can work with fields and properties."}]},{"code":["@Export","var number: Int","","@Export","var AnotherNumber { get { ... } set { ... }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Exported members can specify a default value:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Export","var number: Int = 0","","@Export","var text: String? = nil        \/\/ Allows for nil","","@Export","var greeting = \"Hello World\"   \/\/ Exported field specifies a default value"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Resources and nodes can be exported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Export","public var resource: Resource { ","    get { ","        return myInternalResource","    } ","    set { ","        print (\"Setting my resource\")","    } ","}","","@Export","public var node: Node { ","    get { ","        return myInternalNode","    } ","    set { ","        print (\"Setting the node\")","    } ","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Grouping Exports","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Grouping-Exports"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is possible to group your exported properties inside the Godot Inspector with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the #exportGroup macro. Every exported property after this annotation will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"added to the group.  Start a new group or use #export_group (””) to break out."}]},{"code":["#exportGroup(\"My Properties\")","@Export var number = 3"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also specifiy that only properties with a given prefix be grouped, like","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["#exportGroup(\"My Properties\", prefix: \"health\")","@Export var health_reload_speed = 3"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Groups cannot be nested, use #exportSubgroup to create subgroups within a group.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["#exportSubgroup(\"Extra Properties\")","#export var string = \"\"","#export var flag = false"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Customizing-the-Exported-Value","type":"heading","text":"Customizing the Exported Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can pass a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint","isActive":true},{"text":" parameter to the Export attribute, along with additional","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"data to control how the property is surfaced in the editor.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, to surface the property as a file and trigger the file selector in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"UI, use the ","type":"text"},{"code":".file","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Export(.file)","var GameFile: String? "],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"String as a path to a directory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Export(.dir)","var gameDirectory: String?"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"String as a path to a file, custom filter provided as hint."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export (.file, \"*.txt\")","var GameFile: String?"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using paths in the global filesystem is also possible, but only in scripts in tool mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"String as a path to a PNG file in the global filesystem.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export (.globalFile, \"*.png\")","var toolImage: String?"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"String as a path to a directory in the global filesystem.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Export (.globalDir)","var toolDir: String?"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The multiline annotation tells the editor to show a large input field for editing over multiple lines.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export (.multilineText)","var text: String?"]},{"text":"Limiting editor input ranges","anchor":"Limiting-editor-input-ranges","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using the range property hint allows you to limit what can be input as a value using the editor."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow integer values from 0 to 20."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Export(.range, \"0,20,\")","var number: Int = 0"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow integer values from -10 to 20."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Export(.range, \"-10,20,\")","var number: Int =  0"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow floats from -10 to 20 and snap the value to multiples of 0.2."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export(.range, \"-10,20,0.2\")","var number = 0"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you add the hints ","type":"text"},{"code":"or_greater","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and\/or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"or_less"},{"text":" you can go above or below the limits when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"adjusting the value by typing it instead of using the slider.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["@Export(.range, \"0,100,1,or_greater,or_less\")","var number: Int = 0"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Floats with easing hint","anchor":"Floats-with-easing-hint"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Display a visual representation of the "},{"code":"ease()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function when editing.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Export(.expEasing)","public transitionSpeed: Float = 0"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Colors","level":3,"anchor":"Colors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Regular color given as red-green-blue-alpha value."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Export","var color: Color { get {} set {} }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Color given as red-green-blue value (alpha will always be 1)."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export(.colorNoAlpha)","var color: Color { get {} set {} }"]},{"text":"Nodes","anchor":"Nodes","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since Godot 4.0, nodes can be directly exported without having to use NodePaths."}]},{"code":["@Export","public Node Node { get; set; }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom node classes can also be used, see C# global classes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Exporting NodePaths like in Godot 3.x is still possible, in case you need it:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@Export","var nodePath: NodePath","","public override func _ready() ","{","    var node = GetNode(nodePath)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you find yourself that you do not want to provide manual get\/set properties"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in your export, and want to have an optional for one of the Object types, you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can use something like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Export(.nodeType, \"Camera3D\")","var camera: Camera3D? = nil"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The parameter to "},{"code":".nodeType","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" needs to match the type of the object."}]},{"anchor":"Resources","type":"heading","text":"Resources","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export","var resource: Resource { get {} set {} }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the Inspector, you can then drag and drop a resource file from the FileSystem dock into the variable slot."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Opening the inspector dropdown may result in an extremely long list of possible classes to create, however."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Therefore, if you specify a type derived from Resource such as:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export","var resource: AnimationNode"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The drop-down menu will be limited to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AnimationNode"},{"text":" and all its inherited classes.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Custom resource classes can also be used, see Swift global classes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It must be noted that even if the script is not being run while in the editor, the exported"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"properties are still editable. This can be used in conjunction with a script in “tool” mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Arrays","level":3,"text":"Arrays","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To surface arrays in Godot, use a strong type for it, for example:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Export","var myResources: VariantCollection<Resource>"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Enumeration Values","anchor":"Enumeration-Values"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To surface enumeration values, use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Export(.enum)"},{"text":" marker on your variable,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and it is important that your enumeration conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CaseIterable"},{"text":" and one of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the integral types, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["enum MyEnum: Int, CaseIterable {","    case first","    case second","}","","@Godot","class Sample: Node {","    @Export(.enum)","    var myValue: MyEnum","}"]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Exports","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Exports","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In Godot, class members can be exported. This means their value gets saved along"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the resource (such as the scene) they’re attached to. They will also be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"available for editing in the property editor. Exporting is done by using the"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/GodotObject":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GodotObject"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GodotObject","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/godotobject","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol implemented by the built-in classes in Godot to allow to be wrapped in a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"title":"GodotObject"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RunningInEditor":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/runningineditor","title":"Running Code in the Godot Editor","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RunningInEditor","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"There are cases where you might want some of your Swift code for your extension","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to run while it is being used in the Godot Editor.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/CustomTypes":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/customtypes","title":"Using Custom Types","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"You will typically extend the functionality of your Godot game by creating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"classes that derive from one of the various Godot types and adjust the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior accordingly."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PropertyHint":{"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PropertyHint"}],"title":"PropertyHint","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/propertyhint","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PropertyHint","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PropertyHint","kind":"symbol","abstract":[]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Variant"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variant","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Variant"}],"type":"topic","title":"Variant","abstract":[{"text":"Variant objects box various Godot Objects, you create them with one of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"constructors, and you can retrieve the contents using the various extension"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constructors that are declared on the various types that are wrapped.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Differences":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/differences","title":"SwiftGodot API differences to GDScript","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This document lists some common differences between GDSscript and SwiftGodot."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/AnimationNode":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Base class for ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AnimationTree","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" nodes. Not related to scene nodes."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AnimationNode","title":"AnimationNode","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/animationnode","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AnimationNode","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AnimationNode","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Signals":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/signals","title":"Signals","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Signals in Godot are used by objects to post interesting events that are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"taking place, and can be used by users to easily add behavior and react","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to changes.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/AnimationTree":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AnimationTree","title":"AnimationTree","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AnimationTree","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A node used for advanced animation transitions in an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AnimationPlayer","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AnimationTree","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/animationtree"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variants":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variants","title":"Variants","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variants","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Follow up on the fundamental building block of Godot’s data types.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/BindingNodes":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/bindingnodes","title":"Referencing Nodes from your Scene","abstract":[{"text":"You will find yourself referencing nodes from a scene in your code.   In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GDScript, that is usually achieved by using the dollar sign and the name of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object you want to reference.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes"}}}